    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>American Is Denied Bail</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <dateline>MOSCOW, Aug. 24</dateline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Russian officials deny bail to Edmond Pope, 53, American businessman held on espionage charges (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Russian officials denied bail today to Edmond Pope, 53, an American businessman held on espionage charges, rejecting his lawyer's argument that Mr. Pope has cancer and needs specialized medical treatment.</p>
        <p>Mr. Pope, a former Navy intelligence officer, was arrested in April on charges of trying to buy classified information about the design of a new super-fast torpedo from a Russian science professor. He faces trial in October.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>Russian officials denied bail today to Edmond Pope, 53, an American businessman held on espionage charges, rejecting his lawyer's argument that Mr. Pope has cancer and needs specialized medical treatment.</p>
        <p>Mr. Pope, a former Navy intelligence officer, was arrested in April on charges of trying to buy classified information about the design of a new super-fast torpedo from a Russian science professor. He faces trial in October.</p>
        <p>President Clinton discussed the case in a telephone call with President Vladimir V. Putin last week.</p>
      </block>
